default3. 
defaultBus services in village communities such as Cropwell Bishop are inadequate.  The village is just 8 miles from 
defaultNottingham but the population of around 2000 people is disadvantaged because there is no direct commuter service and no evening services connecting with the city or other local communities.
default&#xa0;
default4. 
defaultLocal authorities have reduced funds available to help subsidi
defaultse bus services in less populated areas. Commercial operators have little interest in less profitable semi rural services
default 
defaultbut are generally making healthy profits from their core routes. 
defaultS
defaultometimes 2 or more operators cover the same core route
default indicating po
defaulttential profits to be made.
defaultIt is considered that Improvements to semi rural bus services can be achieved at very small costs if available resources are redirected by partial regulation and licensing of local area concessions.  
defaultLicensed 
default(franchised) 
defaulto
defaultperat
defaultors would be required to provide
default agreed
default appropriate 
defaultsemi 
defaultrural service
defaults alongside their profitable core routes.
